content:
You can block chats from troublesome customers right from the Salesforce console. For example, if a customer is using abusive language or sending spam messages, you can block that user from starting a new chat.

Available in: Performance Editions and in Developer Edition orgs that were created after June 14, 2012
Available in: Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

To block a chat:
Click the icon.
(Optional) Enter a comment explaining why you’re blocking this visitor.
Click Block.

This ends the chat and blocks any new chat requests coming from that user’s IP address. If your Salesforce org is receiving many spam chats from a particular region, your administrator can block entire ranges of IP addresses. Only a Salesforce admin can unblock an IP address.
title: Blocking Unwanted Chat Customers in Service Cloud
